{"tid":2063000,"cid":5,"subCid":12,"title":"香港蝴蝶效應「打噴嚏」對美國也有影響","createTime":"2020-06-13T14:22:58.000Z","updateTime":"2020-06-14T11:42:01.000Z","uid":186,"like":3,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":10,"replies":[{"pid":"46f3bb6850dd9b6a65c22bd17d07262cd6f76175","tid":2063000,"uid":186,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:22:58.000Z","msg":"陳茂波指本港為美元結算中心「打噴嚏」對美國也有影響<br />\n【Now新聞台】財政司司長陳茂波表示，毋須過份憂慮美國會因為港區國安法禁止香港銀行以美元結算。他指美國在港有不少利益，任何改動都會影響美國企業利益。陳茂波又說這段時間未見資金流出，反而流進本港。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://news.now.com/home/local/player?newsId=394291\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.now.com%2Fhome%2Flocal%2Fplayer%3FnewsId%3D394291&d=8Hffn7AX%2B5q16JKWebZXJnaXPXn3VG1rMaGvML0ROe4%3D&h=0481694a\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.now.com%2Fhome%2Flocal%2Fplayer%3FnewsId%3D394291&h=e8e5cd6c\" target=\"_blank\">https://news.now.com/home/local/player?newsId=394291</a><br />\n<br />\n#每日一篇"},{"pid":"eeefccb4f75bc9bd13eb04807534ad5c81663a62","tid":2063000,"uid":186,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:23:56.000Z","msg":"蝴蝶效應（英語：Butterfly effect）是指在一個動態系統中，初始條件的微小變化，將能帶動整個系統長期且巨大的連鎖反應，是一種混沌的現象。「蝴蝶效應」在混沌學中也常出現。<br />\n<br />\n1963年，羅倫茲發表論文「決定性的非週期流」（Deterministic Nonperiodic Flow），分析了這個效應。這篇論文後來被廣泛引用。[1][2]他也在另一篇期刊文章寫道，「一個氣象學家提及，如果這個理論被證明正確，一隻海鷗扇動翅膀足以永遠改變天氣變化。」[3]在以後的演講和論文中他用了更加有詩意的蝴蝶。對於這個效應最常見的闡述是「一隻蝴蝶在巴西輕拍翅膀，可以導致一個月後德克薩斯州的一場龍捲風。」"},{"pid":"ce4b45bd541b31ffd55f4341decf9307168378c8","tid":2063000,"uid":186,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:24:10.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"0a862d324dc1dc8611f5b28240b2867378ab7bce","tid":2063000,"uid":53524,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:26:16.000Z","msg":"論一篤精如果影響宿主"},{"pid":"83385c03bb152d489864adfe694c141682c29a5a","tid":2063000,"uid":186,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:26:41.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"8019f0b35a2d21f17ea05ad1159879f6e5a809e1","tid":2063000,"uid":123738,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:28:14.000Z","msg":"支那打個冷震美帝即跪啦，成日都驚又唔敢反擊<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/pointing.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n支那狗愈來愈廢"},{"pid":"a573ac9b011889e5952a5bb85ec26c2a2d3a94f8","tid":2063000,"uid":37246,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"quote":{"pid":"eeefccb4f75bc9bd13eb04807534ad5c81663a62","tid":2063000,"uid":186,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:23:56.000Z","msg":"蝴蝶效應（英語：Butterfly effect）是指在一個動態系統中，初始條件的微小變化，將能帶動整個系統長期且巨大的連鎖反應，是一種混沌的現象。「蝴蝶效應」在混沌學中也常出現。<br />\n<br />\n1963年，羅倫茲發表論文「決定性的非週期流」（Deterministic Nonperiodic Flow），分析了這個效應。這篇論文後來被廣泛引用。[1][2]他也在另一篇期刊文章寫道，「一個氣象學家提及，如果這個理論被證明正確，一隻海鷗扇動翅膀足以永遠改變天氣變化。」[3]在以後的演講和論文中他用了更加有詩意的蝴蝶。對於這個效應最常見的闡述是「一隻蝴蝶在巴西輕拍翅膀，可以導致一個月後德克薩斯州的一場龍捲風。」"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:28:18.000Z","msg":"對於這個效應最常見的闡述是「一頂綠帽，可以導致一次世界大戰。」<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"21d34b7f87cdb84bb3aa5edf0f443a20e7bc867a","tid":2063000,"uid":127929,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:32:15.000Z","msg":"會變回力鏢<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />一個大海嘯cum返黎香港<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />然後黑警會死全家<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/mock.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />高可晴之後去日本下海拍AV<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/clap.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />然後14億人就係咁走資去日本揾可晴開單<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/sowhat.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />最後可晴返左香港想借犯法去監獄避世都冇用<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />因為犯法就係犯法，除非你係高可晴<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/whip.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"2733cd32260c391a636a5abe3c87cf741f077339","tid":2063000,"uid":113929,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:35:17.000Z","msg":"我只係知道中国打乞嗤，打到全世界都中哂肺炎"},{"pid":"028b5a682309c8cf89a28a8a5a2e42dd45afd524","tid":2063000,"uid":200663,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:36:54.000Z","msg":"如果這一秒鐘你跟我講從未愛我"},{"pid":"e32630ab543565410dc3c68a0a8018ca57216bd4","tid":2063000,"uid":186,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"a573ac9b011889e5952a5bb85ec26c2a2d3a94f8","tid":2063000,"uid":37246,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"quote":{"pid":"eeefccb4f75bc9bd13eb04807534ad5c81663a62","tid":2063000,"uid":186,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:23:56.000Z","msg":"蝴蝶效應（英語：Butterfly effect）是指在一個動態系統中，初始條件的微小變化，將能帶動整個系統長期且巨大的連鎖反應，是一種混沌的現象。「蝴蝶效應」在混沌學中也常出現。<br />\n<br />\n1963年，羅倫茲發表論文「決定性的非週期流」（Deterministic Nonperiodic Flow），分析了這個效應。這篇論文後來被廣泛引用。[1][2]他也在另一篇期刊文章寫道，「一個氣象學家提及，如果這個理論被證明正確，一隻海鷗扇動翅膀足以永遠改變天氣變化。」[3]在以後的演講和論文中他用了更加有詩意的蝴蝶。對於這個效應最常見的闡述是「一隻蝴蝶在巴西輕拍翅膀，可以導致一個月後德克薩斯州的一場龍捲風。」"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:28:18.000Z","msg":"對於這個效應最常見的闡述是「一頂綠帽，可以導致一次世界大戰。」<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:41:06.000Z","msg":"最強精子"},{"pid":"77a3453178184f33d581d9da5187f924c4c1717b","tid":2063000,"uid":186,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"2733cd32260c391a636a5abe3c87cf741f077339","tid":2063000,"uid":113929,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:35:17.000Z","msg":"我只係知道中国打乞嗤，打到全世界都中哂肺炎"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-13T14:41:19.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"2936e1b138464e6533f47dda46b18a7544a7f7f5","tid":2063000,"uid":163801,"like":0,